tion and trade, but also generates feelings of peripherality that inform women's imaginative construction of other, non-territorial borders to be crossed. Shaped by social class, gender, and the economic and cultural possibilities of political decentralization, the study identifies three borderscopes that orient women's work-related mobility in different directions and bring with them diverse outcomes for the ethnocultural category 'Sambas Malay'.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aMalays (Asian people)xRace identity. 0aSocial mobilityzIndonesia. 0aWomenzIndonesiaxSocial conditions. 0aWomen, MalayxSocial conditions. 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality Studies. 4aSouth East Asia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aMobility, Identity, Malay, Women, Border.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048544936zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048544936423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048544936.jpg  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, 